@prefix : <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#> .
@prefix ba: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor#> .
@prefix be: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteethos#> .
@prefix bf: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteflow#> .
@prefix bc: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/bytecore#> .
@prefix bp: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/bytepqc#> .
@prefix doe: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/doctrine-of-8#> .
@prefix det: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/deterministic-execution#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix time: <http://www.w3.org/2006/time#> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix dct: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix sp: <http://spinrdf.org/sp#> .

<http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm> rdf:type owl:Ontology ;
    dct:title "ByteActor Realm: Foundational Actor Model Execution Environment"@en ;
    dct:description """The comprehensive ontology defining the ByteActor realm - the foundational 
    execution model for all ByteStar computational operations. This ontology establishes the actor 
    model patterns, message-passing semantics, actor lifecycle management, fault tolerance mechanisms,
    supervision trees, location transparency, and ultra-high performance characteristics under the
    Doctrine of 8 constraint system. ByteActor serves as the computational substrate for all ByteStar
    operations, providing deterministic execution guarantees with mathematical certainty."""@en ;
    dct:creator "ByteStar Architecture Foundation"@en ;
    dct:created "2025-08-23T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dct:modified "2025-08-23T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    owl:versionInfo "5.0.0-phase2"@en ;
    dct:license <https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT> ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <http://bytestar.org/docs/byteactor-realm> ;
    owl:imports <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor> ,
                <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteethos> ,
                <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteflow> ,
                <http://bytestar.org/ontology/bytecore> ,
                <http://bytestar.org/ontology/bytepqc> ,
                <http://bytestar.org/ontology/doctrine-of-8> ,
                <http://bytestar.org/ontology/deterministic-execution> ;
    # Foundational execution model declaration
    :hasExecutionModel :ByteActorModel ;
    :hasPerformanceGuarantee doe:TheDoctrineOfEight ;
    :hasDeterminismGuarantee det:ByteStarDeterministicExecution .

#################################################################
#    Core ByteActor Realm Classes
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ByteActorModel
:ByteActorModel rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:label "ByteActor Model"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """The foundational computational model for ByteStar operations based 
               on the actor model pattern. Provides isolated, concurrent computation with 
               message-passing communication and supervision-based fault tolerance."""@en ;
               rdfs:subClassOf ba:ComputationModel ;
               skos:definition """A concurrent computation model where independent actors process 
               messages asynchronously, maintaining isolation and fault tolerance through 
               supervision hierarchies."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#Actor
:Actor rdf:type owl:Class ;
      rdfs:label "ByteActor"@en ;
      rdfs:comment """An autonomous computational entity that processes messages sequentially,
      maintains private state, and communicates only through asynchronous message passing.
      The fundamental unit of computation in the ByteActor realm."""@en ;
      rdfs:subClassOf ba:ComputationalEntity ;
      skos:definition """An isolated computation unit with private state, message queue, 
      and behavior function that processes messages sequentially while maintaining 
      deterministic execution guarantees."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorSystem
:ActorSystem rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:label "Actor System"@en ;
            rdfs:comment """The runtime environment that manages actor lifecycles, message 
            routing, supervision, and resource allocation across the ByteActor realm."""@en ;
            rdfs:subClassOf ba:RuntimeSystem ;
            skos:definition """The foundational runtime that provides actor creation, 
            supervision, message delivery, fault tolerance, and performance monitoring 
            under Doctrine of 8 constraints."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#Message
:Message rdf:type owl:Class ;
        rdfs:label "Actor Message"@en ;
        rdfs:comment """An immutable data structure sent between actors for communication.
        Messages are the only way actors interact, ensuring isolation and determinism."""@en ;
        rdfs:subClassOf ba:CommunicationPrimitive ;
        skos:definition """An immutable, serializable data structure that carries information
        from sender to receiver actor, processed asynchronously in FIFO order."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#Mailbox
:Mailbox rdf:type owl:Class ;
        rdfs:label "Actor Mailbox"@en ;
        rdfs:comment """The message queue associated with each actor that stores incoming 
        messages in FIFO order until processed by the actor's behavior function."""@en ;
        rdfs:subClassOf ba:MessageQueue ;
        skos:definition """A bounded, thread-safe FIFO queue that stores messages for an 
        actor, with overflow handling and backpressure mechanisms."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#Behavior
:Behavior rdf:type owl:Class ;
         rdfs:label "Actor Behavior"@en ;
         rdfs:comment """The computational logic that defines how an actor processes 
         messages and updates its state. Behaviors are pure functions ensuring determinism."""@en ;
         rdfs:subClassOf det:PureFunction ;
         skos:definition """A deterministic function that takes current state and message
         as input, producing new state and optional output messages."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorReference
:ActorReference rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:label "Actor Reference"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """A location-transparent handle for sending messages to an actor,
               enabling communication without knowledge of physical location."""@en ;
               rdfs:subClassOf ba:Reference ;
               skos:definition """An opaque reference that enables message sending to actors
               regardless of their physical location in the distributed system."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Actor Types and Specializations
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ComputeActor
:ComputeActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
             rdfs:subClassOf :Actor ;
             rdfs:label "Compute Actor"@en ;
             rdfs:comment """An actor specialized for CPU-intensive computational tasks,
             optimized for mathematical operations and algorithm execution."""@en ;
             skos:definition """A CPU-bound actor that performs computations, transformations,
             and algorithmic processing with deterministic execution guarantees."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#DataActor
:DataActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
          rdfs:subClassOf :Actor ;
          rdfs:label "Data Actor"@en ;
          rdfs:comment """An actor specialized for data storage, retrieval, and state 
          management with consistency guarantees."""@en ;
          skos:definition """A storage-optimized actor that maintains persistent state,
          handles data operations, and provides consistency guarantees."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#NetworkActor
:NetworkActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
             rdfs:subClassOf :Actor ;
             rdfs:label "Network Actor"@en ;
             rdfs:comment """An actor specialized for network communication, I/O operations,
             and external system integration."""@en ;
             skos:definition """An I/O-bound actor that handles network communication,
             external service integration, and protocol translation."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#SupervisorActor
:SupervisorActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf :Actor ;
                rdfs:label "Supervisor Actor"@en ;
                rdfs:comment """An actor that manages the lifecycle and fault tolerance 
                of child actors through supervision strategies."""@en ;
                skos:definition """A management actor that creates, monitors, and restarts
                child actors according to supervision policies."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#RouterActor
:RouterActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:subClassOf :Actor ;
            rdfs:label "Router Actor"@en ;
            rdfs:comment """An actor that distributes messages across multiple worker 
            actors using routing strategies for load balancing."""@en ;
            skos:definition """A distribution actor that routes messages to worker pools
            using round-robin, consistent hashing, or custom routing logic."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#GuardianActor
:GuardianActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
              rdfs:subClassOf :SupervisorActor ;
              rdfs:label "Guardian Actor"@en ;
              rdfs:comment """The root supervisor actor that oversees the entire actor 
              system hierarchy and handles system-level failures."""@en ;
              skos:definition """The top-level supervisor that manages system lifecycle,
              handles root failures, and ensures system resilience."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Actor Lifecycle Management
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorLifecycle
:ActorLifecycle rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:label "Actor Lifecycle"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """The complete lifecycle of an actor from creation to 
               termination, including all state transitions and events."""@en ;
               rdfs:subClassOf ba:LifecycleProcess ;
               skos:definition """The managed progression of actor states: creation,
               initialization, active processing, stopping, and termination."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorCreation
:ActorCreation rdf:type owl:Class ;
              rdfs:subClassOf :ActorLifecycle ;
              rdfs:label "Actor Creation"@en ;
              rdfs:comment """The process of creating a new actor instance with 
              initialization parameters and supervision context."""@en ;
              skos:definition """The instantiation phase where actors are created,
              initialized with state, and registered in the supervision hierarchy."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorExecution
:ActorExecution rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:subClassOf :ActorLifecycle ;
               rdfs:label "Actor Execution"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """The active processing phase where actors receive and 
               process messages according to their behavior function."""@en ;
               skos:definition """The primary operational phase where actors process
               messages, update state, and send output messages."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorTermination
:ActorTermination rdf:type owl:Class ;
                 rdfs:subClassOf :ActorLifecycle ;
                 rdfs:label "Actor Termination"@en ;
                 rdfs:comment """The controlled shutdown phase where actors complete 
                 processing, clean up resources, and notify supervisors."""@en ;
                 skos:definition """The cleanup phase where actors finish processing,
                 release resources, and notify supervisors of termination."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorState
:ActorState rdf:type owl:Class ;
           rdfs:label "Actor State"@en ;
           rdfs:comment """The internal state maintained by an actor, accessible 
           only through message processing and never shared directly."""@en ;
           rdfs:subClassOf det:ImmutableState ;
           skos:definition """The private data maintained by an actor, modified only
           through message processing with immutability guarantees."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Message-Passing Semantics
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#MessagePassing
:MessagePassing rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:label "Message Passing"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """The communication paradigm where actors interact 
               exclusively through asynchronous message exchange."""@en ;
               rdfs:subClassOf ba:CommunicationParadigm ;
               skos:definition """Asynchronous communication pattern where actors send
               immutable messages without blocking, ensuring isolation and determinism."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#MessageDelivery
:MessageDelivery rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:label "Message Delivery"@en ;
                rdfs:comment """The process of routing and delivering messages from 
                sender actors to recipient actors through the system."""@en ;
                rdfs:subClassOf ba:DeliveryMechanism ;
                skos:definition """The reliable transport of messages with ordering
                guarantees, delivery semantics, and fault tolerance."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#MessageOrdering
:MessageOrdering rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:label "Message Ordering"@en ;
                rdfs:comment """The guarantees about message delivery order between 
                specific sender-receiver pairs."""@en ;
                rdfs:subClassOf ba:OrderingGuarantee ;
                skos:definition """FIFO ordering guarantee for messages between the same
                sender-receiver pair, ensuring deterministic processing."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#MessageSerialization
:MessageSerialization rdf:type owl:Class ;
                     rdfs:label "Message Serialization"@en ;
                     rdfs:comment """The process of converting messages to/from binary 
                     format for network transport and persistence."""@en ;
                     rdfs:subClassOf ba:SerializationMechanism ;
                     skos:definition """Deterministic binary encoding/decoding of messages
                     with version compatibility and integrity verification."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Fault Tolerance and Error Handling
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#FaultTolerance
:FaultTolerance rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:label "Fault Tolerance"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """The system capability to continue operation despite 
               individual actor failures through isolation and supervision."""@en ;
               rdfs:subClassOf ba:ResilienceMechanism ;
               skos:definition """Error containment and recovery through actor isolation,
               supervision hierarchies, and automatic restart strategies."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#SupervisionStrategy
:SupervisionStrategy rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:label "Supervision Strategy"@en ;
                    rdfs:comment """A policy that defines how supervisors respond to 
                    child actor failures and exceptions."""@en ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf ba:FaultHandlingPolicy ;
                    skos:definition """A declarative policy specifying restart behavior,
                    escalation rules, and recovery actions for failed actors."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#RestartStrategy
:RestartStrategy rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf :SupervisionStrategy ;
                rdfs:label "Restart Strategy"@en ;
                rdfs:comment """A supervision strategy that restarts failed actors 
                with fresh state and behavior."""@en ;
                skos:definition """Automatic recreation of failed actors with clean state,
                discarding corrupted state and resuming operation."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ResumeStrategy
:ResumeStrategy rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:subClassOf :SupervisionStrategy ;
               rdfs:label "Resume Strategy"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """A supervision strategy that continues actor operation 
               despite failures, preserving current state."""@en ;
               skos:definition """Continuation of actor processing with existing state,
               ignoring the failure and continuing message processing."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#StopStrategy
:StopStrategy rdf:type owl:Class ;
             rdfs:subClassOf :SupervisionStrategy ;
             rdfs:label "Stop Strategy"@en ;
             rdfs:comment """A supervision strategy that terminates failed actors 
             without restart, removing them from the system."""@en ;
             skos:definition """Permanent termination of failed actors with cleanup
             and notification to dependent components."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#EscalateStrategy
:EscalateStrategy rdf:type owl:Class ;
                 rdfs:subClassOf :SupervisionStrategy ;
                 rdfs:label "Escalate Strategy"@en ;
                 rdfs:comment """A supervision strategy that passes failures up to 
                 parent supervisors for higher-level handling."""@en ;
                 skos:definition """Delegation of failure handling to parent supervisors
                 when local recovery strategies are insufficient."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#SupervisionTree
:SupervisionTree rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:label "Supervision Tree"@en ;
                rdfs:comment """A hierarchical structure of supervisor actors that 
                provides fault tolerance through layered supervision."""@en ;
                rdfs:subClassOf ba:HierarchicalStructure ;
                skos:definition """A tree structure where each supervisor manages child
                actors, providing fault isolation and recovery at multiple levels."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Location Transparency and Distribution
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#LocationTransparency
:LocationTransparency rdf:type owl:Class ;
                     rdfs:label "Location Transparency"@en ;
                     rdfs:comment """The property that actors can communicate without 
                     knowledge of physical location or network topology."""@en ;
                     rdfs:subClassOf ba:TransparencyProperty ;
                     skos:definition """Uniform communication semantics regardless of
                     whether actors are local, remote, or distributed across nodes."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorPlacement
:ActorPlacement rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:label "Actor Placement"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """The process of determining where actors should be 
               instantiated in a distributed system."""@en ;
               rdfs:subClassOf ba:PlacementStrategy ;
               skos:definition """Strategic placement of actors across nodes based on
               resource requirements, network topology, and performance constraints."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorMigration
:ActorMigration rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:label "Actor Migration"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """The process of moving actors between nodes during 
               runtime for load balancing and optimization."""@en ;
               rdfs:subClassOf ba:MigrationMechanism ;
               skos:definition """Live migration of actors with state preservation,
               reference updates, and minimal service interruption."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#RemoteReference
:RemoteReference rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf :ActorReference ;
                rdfs:label "Remote Actor Reference"@en ;
                rdfs:comment """A reference to an actor located on a different node 
                in the distributed system."""@en ;
                skos:definition """A network-transparent reference enabling message
                sending to actors on remote nodes with automatic serialization."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#LocalReference
:LocalReference rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:subClassOf :ActorReference ;
               rdfs:label "Local Actor Reference"@en ;
               rdfs:comment """A reference to an actor located on the same node, 
               enabling optimized local message delivery."""@en ;
               skos:definition """An optimized reference for same-node actors with
               direct memory access and zero-copy message passing."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Performance Characteristics under Doctrine of 8
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#PerformanceGuarantee
:PerformanceGuarantee rdf:type owl:Class ;
                     rdfs:label "ByteActor Performance Guarantee"@en ;
                     rdfs:comment """Performance guarantees provided by the ByteActor 
                     realm under the Doctrine of 8 constraint system."""@en ;
                     rdfs:subClassOf doe:PerformanceClassification ;
                     skos:definition """Deterministic performance bounds for actor
                     operations with mathematical guarantees under strict constraints."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#MessageProcessingGuarantee
:MessageProcessingGuarantee rdf:type owl:Class ;
                           rdfs:subClassOf :PerformanceGuarantee ;
                           rdfs:label "Message Processing Guarantee"@en ;
                           rdfs:comment """Guarantee that message processing completes 
                           within Doctrine of 8 tick constraints."""@en ;
                           skos:definition """Mathematical guarantee that actor message
                           processing completes within 8 CPU ticks maximum."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorCreationGuarantee
:ActorCreationGuarantee rdf:type owl:Class ;
                       rdfs:subClassOf :PerformanceGuarantee ;
                       rdfs:label "Actor Creation Guarantee"@en ;
                       rdfs:comment """Guarantee that actor creation and initialization 
                       completes within performance bounds."""@en ;
                       skos:definition """Bounded time guarantee for actor instantiation,
                       initialization, and supervision registration."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#MessageDeliveryGuarantee
:MessageDeliveryGuarantee rdf:type owl:Class ;
                         rdfs:subClassOf :PerformanceGuarantee ;
                         rdfs:label "Message Delivery Guarantee"@en ;
                         rdfs:comment """Guarantee that message delivery between actors 
                         completes within bounded time."""@en ;
                         skos:definition """Deterministic delivery time bounds for
                         messages with acknowledgment and retry mechanisms."""@en .

#################################################################
#    PQC Security Integration
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#SecureActor
:SecureActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:subClassOf :Actor ;
            rdfs:label "Post-Quantum Secure Actor"@en ;
            rdfs:comment """An actor enhanced with post-quantum cryptographic 
            capabilities for secure communication and computation."""@en ;
            skos:definition """A cryptographically enhanced actor with PQC message
            encryption, digital signatures, and secure state management."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#CryptographicMessage
:CryptographicMessage rdf:type owl:Class ;
                     rdfs:subClassOf :Message ;
                     rdfs:label "Cryptographic Message"@en ;
                     rdfs:comment """A message protected with post-quantum cryptographic 
                     algorithms for confidentiality and integrity."""@en ;
                     skos:definition """An encrypted and signed message using PQC
                     algorithms with perfect forward secrecy and replay protection."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#SecureMailbox
:SecureMailbox rdf:type owl:Class ;
              rdfs:subClassOf :Mailbox ;
              rdfs:label "Secure Mailbox"@en ;
              rdfs:comment """A cryptographically protected mailbox that ensures 
              message confidentiality and authenticity."""@en ;
              skos:definition """An encrypted message queue with access control,
              integrity verification, and audit logging capabilities."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Deterministic Execution Integration
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#DeterministicActor
:DeterministicActor rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   rdfs:subClassOf :Actor ,
                                   det:DeterministicOperation ;
                   rdfs:label "Deterministic Actor"@en ;
                   rdfs:comment """An actor that provides mathematical guarantees of 
                   deterministic behavior for identical inputs."""@en ;
                   skos:definition """An actor with provable deterministic behavior,
                   producing identical outputs for identical message sequences."""@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ReproducibleExecution
:ReproducibleExecution rdf:type owl:Class ;
                      rdfs:subClassOf det:ReproducibleResult ;
                      rdfs:label "Reproducible Actor Execution"@en ;
                      rdfs:comment """Actor execution that can be exactly reproduced 
                      with identical results across multiple runs."""@en ;
                      skos:definition """Bit-identical execution reproducibility with
                      complete state and message trace capture."""@en .

#################################################################
#    Object Properties
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#hasMailbox
:hasMailbox rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ,
                     owl:FunctionalProperty ;
           rdfs:domain :Actor ;
           rdfs:range :Mailbox ;
           rdfs:label "has mailbox"@en ;
           rdfs:comment "Associates an actor with its message queue."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#hasBehavior
:hasBehavior rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ,
                      owl:FunctionalProperty ;
            rdfs:domain :Actor ;
            rdfs:range :Behavior ;
            rdfs:label "has behavior"@en ;
            rdfs:comment "Associates an actor with its message processing function."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#hasState
:hasState rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ,
                   owl:FunctionalProperty ;
         rdfs:domain :Actor ;
         rdfs:range :ActorState ;
         rdfs:label "has state"@en ;
         rdfs:comment "Associates an actor with its internal state."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#sendsTo
:sendsTo rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
        rdfs:domain :Actor ;
        rdfs:range :ActorReference ;
        rdfs:label "sends to"@en ;
        rdfs:comment "Indicates that an actor sends messages to another actor."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#receivesFrom
:receivesFrom rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
             rdfs:domain :Actor ;
             rdfs:range :ActorReference ;
             rdfs:label "receives from"@en ;
             rdfs:comment "Indicates that an actor receives messages from another actor."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#supervisedBy
:supervisedBy rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
             rdfs:domain :Actor ;
             rdfs:range :SupervisorActor ;
             rdfs:label "supervised by"@en ;
             rdfs:comment "Indicates the supervisor responsible for an actor."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#supervises
:supervises rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
           rdfs:domain :SupervisorActor ;
           rdfs:range :Actor ;
           rdfs:label "supervises"@en ;
           rdfs:comment "Indicates the actors supervised by a supervisor."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#hasSupervisionStrategy
:hasSupervisionStrategy rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ,
                                 owl:FunctionalProperty ;
                       rdfs:domain :SupervisorActor ;
                       rdfs:range :SupervisionStrategy ;
                       rdfs:label "has supervision strategy"@en ;
                       rdfs:comment "Associates a supervisor with its fault handling strategy."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#locatedAt
:locatedAt rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
          rdfs:domain :Actor ;
          rdfs:range ba:Node ;
          rdfs:label "located at"@en ;
          rdfs:comment "Indicates the physical node where an actor is located."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#referencedBy
:referencedBy rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
             rdfs:domain :Actor ;
             rdfs:range :ActorReference ;
             rdfs:label "referenced by"@en ;
             rdfs:comment "Associates an actor with its reference handle."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#processesMessage
:processesMessage rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
                 rdfs:domain :Actor ;
                 rdfs:range :Message ;
                 rdfs:label "processes message"@en ;
                 rdfs:comment "Indicates that an actor processes a specific message."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#hasPerformanceGuarantee
:hasPerformanceGuarantee rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
                        rdfs:domain :Actor ;
                        rdfs:range :PerformanceGuarantee ;
                        rdfs:label "has performance guarantee"@en ;
                        rdfs:comment "Associates an actor with its performance guarantees."@en .

#################################################################
#    Data Properties
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#actorId
:actorId rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                  owl:FunctionalProperty ;
        rdfs:domain :Actor ;
        rdfs:range xsd:string ;
        rdfs:label "actor ID"@en ;
        rdfs:comment "Unique identifier for an actor instance."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#mailboxCapacity
:mailboxCapacity rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                          owl:FunctionalProperty ;
                rdfs:domain :Mailbox ;
                rdfs:range xsd:positiveInteger ;
                rdfs:label "mailbox capacity"@en ;
                rdfs:comment "Maximum number of messages the mailbox can hold."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#messageCount
:messageCount rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                       owl:FunctionalProperty ;
             rdfs:domain :Mailbox ;
             rdfs:range xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
             rdfs:label "message count"@en ;
             rdfs:comment "Current number of messages in the mailbox."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#creationTimestamp
:creationTimestamp rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                            owl:FunctionalProperty ;
                  rdfs:domain :Actor ;
                  rdfs:range xsd:dateTime ;
                  rdfs:label "creation timestamp"@en ;
                  rdfs:comment "Timestamp when the actor was created."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#lastMessageTimestamp
:lastMessageTimestamp rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                               owl:FunctionalProperty ;
                     rdfs:domain :Actor ;
                     rdfs:range xsd:dateTime ;
                     rdfs:label "last message timestamp"@en ;
                     rdfs:comment "Timestamp of the last processed message."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#processingTime
:processingTime rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ;
               rdfs:domain :Actor ;
               rdfs:range xsd:long ;
               rdfs:label "processing time"@en ;
               rdfs:comment "Time taken to process a message in CPU ticks."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#isActive
:isActive rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                   owl:FunctionalProperty ;
         rdfs:domain :Actor ;
         rdfs:range xsd:boolean ;
         rdfs:label "is active"@en ;
         rdfs:comment "Indicates whether the actor is currently active."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#restartCount
:restartCount rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                       owl:FunctionalProperty ;
             rdfs:domain :Actor ;
             rdfs:range xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
             rdfs:label "restart count"@en ;
             rdfs:comment "Number of times the actor has been restarted."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#maxProcessingTicks
:maxProcessingTicks rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                             owl:FunctionalProperty ;
                   rdfs:domain :PerformanceGuarantee ;
                   rdfs:range xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
                   rdfs:label "max processing ticks"@en ;
                   rdfs:comment "Maximum CPU ticks allowed for processing."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#nodeId
:nodeId rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ,
                 owl:FunctionalProperty ;
       rdfs:domain ba:Node ;
       rdfs:range xsd:string ;
       rdfs:label "node ID"@en ;
       rdfs:comment "Unique identifier for a system node."@en .

#################################################################
#    Individuals - Standard Actor Types
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#SystemGuardian
:SystemGuardian rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         :GuardianActor ;
               rdfs:label "System Guardian"@en ;
               rdfs:comment "The root guardian actor for the entire ByteActor system."@en ;
               :actorId "system-guardian" ;
               :isActive "true"^^xsd:boolean .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#UserGuardian
:UserGuardian rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                       :GuardianActor ;
             rdfs:label "User Guardian"@en ;
             rdfs:comment "Guardian actor for user-created actors."@en ;
             :actorId "user-guardian" ;
             :supervisedBy :SystemGuardian ;
             :isActive "true"^^xsd:boolean .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#DeadLetterActor
:DeadLetterActor rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                          :Actor ;
                rdfs:label "Dead Letter Actor"@en ;
                rdfs:comment "Actor that handles undeliverable messages."@en ;
                :actorId "dead-letter" ;
                :supervisedBy :SystemGuardian ;
                :isActive "true"^^xsd:boolean .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#StandardSupervisionStrategy
:StandardSupervisionStrategy rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                      :RestartStrategy ;
                            rdfs:label "Standard Supervision Strategy"@en ;
                            rdfs:comment "Default restart-based supervision strategy."@en .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#StandardPerformanceGuarantee
:StandardPerformanceGuarantee rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                       :MessageProcessingGuarantee ;
                             rdfs:label "Standard Performance Guarantee"@en ;
                             rdfs:comment "Standard 8-tick message processing guarantee."@en ;
                             :maxProcessingTicks "8"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger .

#################################################################
#    SHACL Shapes for Validation
#################################################################

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#ActorShape
:ActorShape rdf:type sh:NodeShape ;
           sh:targetClass :Actor ;
           rdfs:label "Actor Shape"@en ;
           rdfs:comment "Validates ByteActor properties and constraints."@en ;
           sh:property [
               sh:path :actorId ;
               sh:datatype xsd:string ;
               sh:minCount 1 ;
               sh:maxCount 1 ;
               sh:message "Every actor must have exactly one unique actor ID."@en
           ] ;
           sh:property [
               sh:path :hasMailbox ;
               sh:class :Mailbox ;
               sh:minCount 1 ;
               sh:maxCount 1 ;
               sh:message "Every actor must have exactly one mailbox."@en
           ] ;
           sh:property [
               sh:path :hasBehavior ;
               sh:class :Behavior ;
               sh:minCount 1 ;
               sh:maxCount 1 ;
               sh:message "Every actor must have exactly one behavior function."@en
           ] ;
           sh:property [
               sh:path :hasState ;
               sh:class :ActorState ;
               sh:minCount 1 ;
               sh:maxCount 1 ;
               sh:message "Every actor must have exactly one state container."@en
           ] ;
           sh:property [
               sh:path :supervisedBy ;
               sh:class :SupervisorActor ;
               sh:minCount 1 ;
               sh:maxCount 1 ;
               sh:message "Every actor must have exactly one supervisor."@en
           ] ;
           sh:property [
               sh:path :isActive ;
               sh:datatype xsd:boolean ;
               sh:minCount 1 ;
               sh:maxCount 1 ;
               sh:message "Every actor must have an active status."@en
           ] .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#MailboxShape
:MailboxShape rdf:type sh:NodeShape ;
             sh:targetClass :Mailbox ;
             rdfs:label "Mailbox Shape"@en ;
             rdfs:comment "Validates mailbox capacity and message constraints."@en ;
             sh:property [
                 sh:path :mailboxCapacity ;
                 sh:datatype xsd:positiveInteger ;
                 sh:minCount 1 ;
                 sh:maxCount 1 ;
                 sh:minInclusive 1 ;
                 sh:message "Mailbox must have a positive capacity."@en
             ] ;
             sh:property [
                 sh:path :messageCount ;
                 sh:datatype xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
                 sh:minCount 1 ;
                 sh:maxCount 1 ;
                 sh:message "Mailbox must track current message count."@en
             ] .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#SupervisorShape
:SupervisorShape rdf:type sh:NodeShape ;
                sh:targetClass :SupervisorActor ;
                rdfs:label "Supervisor Shape"@en ;
                rdfs:comment "Validates supervisor-specific constraints."@en ;
                sh:property [
                    sh:path :hasSupervisionStrategy ;
                    sh:class :SupervisionStrategy ;
                    sh:minCount 1 ;
                    sh:maxCount 1 ;
                    sh:message "Every supervisor must have exactly one supervision strategy."@en
                ] ;
                sh:property [
                    sh:path :supervises ;
                    sh:class :Actor ;
                    sh:minCount 0 ;
                    sh:message "Supervisor can supervise zero or more actors."@en
                ] .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#PerformanceGuaranteeShape
:PerformanceGuaranteeShape rdf:type sh:NodeShape ;
                          sh:targetClass :PerformanceGuarantee ;
                          rdfs:label "Performance Guarantee Shape"@en ;
                          rdfs:comment "Validates performance guarantee constraints."@en ;
                          sh:property [
                              sh:path :maxProcessingTicks ;
                              sh:datatype xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
                              sh:minCount 1 ;
                              sh:maxCount 1 ;
                              sh:maxInclusive 8 ;
                              sh:message "Performance guarantee must not exceed 8 ticks (Doctrine of 8)."@en
                          ] .

###  http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#DeterministicActorShape
:DeterministicActorShape rdf:type sh:NodeShape ;
                        sh:targetClass :DeterministicActor ;
                        rdfs:label "Deterministic Actor Shape"@en ;
                        rdfs:comment "Validates deterministic actor properties."@en ;
                        sh:property [
                            sh:path det:isDeterministic ;
                            sh:datatype xsd:boolean ;
                            sh:hasValue "true"^^xsd:boolean ;
                            sh:message "Deterministic actors must have isDeterministic = true."@en
                        ] ;
                        sh:property [
                            sh:path det:hasInputHash ;
                            sh:datatype xsd:string ;
                            sh:pattern "^[a-fA-F0-9]{64}$" ;
                            sh:message "Deterministic actor must have valid SHA-256 input hash."@en
                        ] ;
                        sh:property [
                            sh:path det:hasOutputHash ;
                            sh:datatype xsd:string ;
                            sh:pattern "^[a-fA-F0-9]{64}$" ;
                            sh:message "Deterministic actor must have valid SHA-256 output hash."@en
                        ] .

#################################################################
#    Axioms and Rules
#################################################################

# Axiom: Every actor must have a supervisor (except system guardian)
[] rdf:type owl:Class ;
   owl:equivalentClass [
       rdf:type owl:Class ;
       owl:intersectionOf (
           :Actor
           [
               rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
               owl:onProperty :supervisedBy ;
               owl:minCardinality 0
           ]
       )
   ] ;
   owl:disjointWith [
       rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
       owl:onProperty :actorId ;
       owl:hasValue "system-guardian"
   ] ;
   rdfs:subClassOf [
       rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
       owl:onProperty :supervisedBy ;
       owl:minCardinality 1
   ] .

# Axiom: Actors process messages within Doctrine of 8 constraints
:Actor rdfs:subClassOf [
    rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
    owl:onProperty :hasPerformanceGuarantee ;
    owl:someValuesFrom :PerformanceGuarantee
] .

# Axiom: Deterministic actors provide mathematical certainty
:DeterministicActor rdfs:subClassOf det:MathematicalCertainty .

# Axiom: Secure actors integrate PQC capabilities
:SecureActor rdfs:subClassOf [
    rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
    owl:onProperty bp:hasPQCCapability ;
    owl:someValuesFrom bp:PQCAlgorithm
] .

# Axiom: Supervision strategies are applied by supervisors
:SupervisorActor rdfs:subClassOf [
    rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
    owl:onProperty :hasSupervisionStrategy ;
    owl:someValuesFrom :SupervisionStrategy
] .

#################################################################
#    SPARQL Queries for Actor System Management
#################################################################

# Query 1: Find all actors supervised by a specific supervisor
:findSupervisionHierarchyQuery rdf:type sp:Query ;
    rdfs:label "Find Supervision Hierarchy"@en ;
    sp:text """
    PREFIX : <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#>
    
    SELECT ?supervisor ?actor ?strategy ?level WHERE {
        ?actor :supervisedBy ?supervisor .
        ?supervisor :hasSupervisionStrategy ?strategy .
        OPTIONAL {
            ?supervisor :supervisedBy ?parentSupervisor .
            BIND(1 AS ?level)
        }
        OPTIONAL {
            ?supervisor :supervisedBy ?parentSupervisor .
            ?parentSupervisor :supervisedBy ?grandParent .
            BIND(2 AS ?level)
        }
    }
    ORDER BY ?level ?supervisor
    """ .

# Query 2: Monitor actor performance against Doctrine of 8
:actorPerformanceMonitorQuery rdf:type sp:Query ;
    rdfs:label "Monitor Actor Performance"@en ;
    sp:text """
    PREFIX : <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#>
    PREFIX doe: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/doctrine-of-8#>
    
    SELECT ?actor ?processingTime ?maxTicks ?violation WHERE {
        ?actor a :Actor ;
               :processingTime ?processingTime ;
               :hasPerformanceGuarantee ?guarantee .
        ?guarantee :maxProcessingTicks ?maxTicks .
        BIND(IF(?processingTime > ?maxTicks, "VIOLATION", "COMPLIANT") AS ?violation)
    }
    ORDER BY DESC(?processingTime)
    """ .

# Query 3: Find failed actors and restart counts
:failureAnalysisQuery rdf:type sp:Query ;
    rdfs:label "Analyze Actor Failures"@en ;
    sp:text """
    PREFIX : <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#>
    
    SELECT ?actor ?restartCount ?supervisor ?strategy ?isActive WHERE {
        ?actor :restartCount ?restartCount ;
               :supervisedBy ?supervisor ;
               :isActive ?isActive .
        ?supervisor :hasSupervisionStrategy ?strategy .
        FILTER (?restartCount > 0)
    }
    ORDER BY DESC(?restartCount)
    """ .

# Query 4: Location distribution analysis
:locationAnalysisQuery rdf:type sp:Query ;
    rdfs:label "Actor Location Distribution"@en ;
    sp:text """
    PREFIX : <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#>
    PREFIX ba: <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor#>
    
    SELECT ?node (COUNT(?actor) AS ?actorCount) ?nodeId WHERE {
        ?actor :locatedAt ?node .
        ?node :nodeId ?nodeId .
    }
    GROUP BY ?node ?nodeId
    ORDER BY DESC(?actorCount)
    """ .

# Query 5: Message processing statistics
:messageProcessingStatsQuery rdf:type sp:Query ;
    rdfs:label "Message Processing Statistics"@en ;
    sp:text """
    PREFIX : <http://bytestar.org/ontology/byteactor-realm#>
    
    SELECT ?actor ?messageCount ?avgProcessingTime ?lastActivity WHERE {
        ?actor :hasMailbox ?mailbox ;
               :lastMessageTimestamp ?lastActivity .
        ?mailbox :messageCount ?messageCount .
        OPTIONAL {
            SELECT ?actor (AVG(?time) AS ?avgProcessingTime) WHERE {
                ?actor :processingTime ?time .
            }
            GROUP BY ?actor
        }
    }
    ORDER BY DESC(?messageCount)
    """ .

#################################################################
#    Integration Examples
#################################################################

# Example 1: High-Performance Compute Actor
:HighPerformanceComputeExample rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                        :ComputeActor ,
                                        :DeterministicActor ;
                              rdfs:label "High-Performance Compute Actor Example"@en ;
                              rdfs:comment "Example of a compute actor with deterministic guarantees."@en ;
                              :actorId "hp-compute-001" ;
                              :supervisedBy :UserGuardian ;
                              :hasPerformanceGuarantee :StandardPerformanceGuarantee ;
                              det:isDeterministic "true"^^xsd:boolean ;
                              :isActive "true"^^xsd:boolean ;
                              :restartCount "0"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger .

# Example 2: Secure Data Actor with PQC
:SecureDataExample rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                            :DataActor ,
                            :SecureActor ;
                  rdfs:label "Secure Data Actor Example"@en ;
                  rdfs:comment "Example of a data actor with post-quantum security."@en ;
                  :actorId "secure-data-001" ;
                  :supervisedBy :UserGuardian ;
                  :hasPerformanceGuarantee :StandardPerformanceGuarantee ;
                  :isActive "true"^^xsd:boolean ;
                  :restartCount "0"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger .

# Example 3: Network Actor with Location Transparency
:NetworkActorExample rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                              :NetworkActor ;
                    rdfs:label "Network Actor Example"@en ;
                    rdfs:comment "Example of a network actor with location transparency."@en ;
                    :actorId "network-gateway-001" ;
                    :supervisedBy :UserGuardian ;
                    :hasPerformanceGuarantee :StandardPerformanceGuarantee ;
                    :isActive "true"^^xsd:boolean ;
                    :restartCount "0"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger .

#################################################################
#    Documentation and Usage Guidelines
#################################################################

:UsageGuidelines rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "ByteActor Usage Guidelines"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Guidelines for proper usage of the ByteActor realm including
    best practices, performance optimization, and fault tolerance patterns."""@en .

:BestPractices rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "ByteActor Best Practices"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """
    1. Keep actors lightweight with minimal state
    2. Use immutable messages for deterministic processing
    3. Design supervision hierarchies for fault isolation
    4. Apply Doctrine of 8 constraints to all operations
    5. Implement proper backpressure handling
    6. Use location transparency for scalability
    7. Apply PQC security for sensitive operations
    8. Monitor performance continuously
    9. Design for graceful degradation
    10. Implement comprehensive logging and tracing
    """@en .

#################################################################
#    Version Information and Metadata
#################################################################

: rdfs:comment """
ByteActor Realm Ontology Version History:

v5.0.0-phase2 (2025-08-23):
- Comprehensive actor model execution environment
- Full actor lifecycle management
- Message-passing semantics with ordering guarantees
- Supervision trees and fault tolerance mechanisms
- Location transparency and distribution support
- Performance guarantees under Doctrine of 8
- PQC security integration
- Deterministic execution guarantees
- Complete SHACL validation framework
- SPARQL monitoring and management queries

This ontology establishes ByteActor as the foundational execution model
for all ByteStar computational operations. It provides:

Key Features:
1. Actor Model Implementation: Complete actor system with isolation
2. Fault Tolerance: Supervision trees with automatic recovery
3. Performance Guarantees: Doctrine of 8 compliance
4. Deterministic Execution: Mathematical certainty guarantees
5. Security Integration: Post-quantum cryptographic protection
6. Location Transparency: Distributed system support
7. Monitoring & Management: Complete observability

Actor Types:
- ComputeActor: CPU-intensive computations
- DataActor: State management and persistence
- NetworkActor: I/O and external integration
- SupervisorActor: Fault tolerance management
- RouterActor: Load balancing and distribution
- GuardianActor: System-level supervision

Performance Characteristics:
- Message processing: ≤8 ticks maximum
- Actor creation: Bounded time guarantee
- Message delivery: Deterministic latency
- Fault recovery: Automatic and bounded

Integration Points:
- ByteCore: Kernel operation execution
- ByteFlow: Workflow orchestration
- ByteEthos: Governance and compliance
- BytePQC: Cryptographic operations

This ontology provides the computational foundation that enables ByteStar
to achieve ultra-high performance while maintaining deterministic behavior,
fault tolerance, and security guarantees across distributed systems.
"""@en .

#################################################################
#    End of ByteActor Realm Ontology
#################################################################